    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently we have these:\r\n\r\n```\r\n==============================================================================\r\n5. Text object motions\t\t\t\t\t*object-motions*\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t*(*\r\n(\t\t\t[count] |sentence|s backward.  |exclusive| motion.\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t*)*\r\n)\t\t\t[count] |sentence|s forward.  |exclusive| motion.\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t*{*\r\n{\t\t\t[count] |paragraph|s backward.  |exclusive| motion.\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t*}*\r\n}\t\t\t[count] |paragraph|s forward.  |exclusive| motion.\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t*]]*\r\n]]\t\t\t[count] |section|s forward or to the next \"{\" in the\r\n\t\t\tfirst column.  When used after an operator, then also\r\n\t\t\tstops below a \"}\" in the first column.  |exclusive|\r\n\t\t\tNote that |exclusive-linewise| often applies.\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t*][*\r\n][\t\t\t[count] |section|s forward or to the next '}' in the\r\n\t\t\tfirst column.  |exclusive|\r\n\t\t\tNote that |exclusive-linewise| often applies.\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t*[[*\r\n[[\t\t\t[count] |section|s backward or to the previous \"{\" in\r\n\t\t\tthe first column.  |exclusive|\r\n\t\t\tNote that |exclusive-linewise| often applies.\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t*[]*\r\n[]\t\t\t[count] |section|s backward or to the previous \"}\" in\r\n\t\t\tthe first column.  |exclusive|\r\n\t\t\tNote that |exclusive-linewise| often applies.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nHaving a bunch of motions centred around the sentences, paragraphs and `{}` (aka \"section\") characters obviously isn't great.\r\n\r\n### Proposal\r\n\r\nUse Treesitter to define `@block` (instead of paragraph) and `@section` (instead of section) which these mappings can be used to navigate.\r\n\r\nOther suggestions welcome.\r\n\r\nRelated: #8544\r\n",
